---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Permissions - SqueezyAgent"
  description="Draft permissions docs for SqueezyAgent."
  activeDoc="/docs/permissions/"
  heading="Permissions"
  lead="A local agent should make mutation explicit and keep cheap semantic reads fast."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <span class="status-pill">draft</span>
    <h2>Permission posture</h2>
    <p>
      Read-only semantic queries should be cheap and low-friction. File writes,
      shell commands, web access, and destructive operations should remain gated
      by mode and user policy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Current foundation</h2>
    <p>
      Edit and shell tools route through allow, ask, or deny policy. Web search
      and fetch are also permission-gated, with host-visible approval summaries
      and bounded response sizes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Structured denial is part of the loop</h2>
    <p>
      When a write or web fetch is denied, the model receives a structured tool
      result instead of guessing what happened. The file or network request does
      not proceed, and the agent can continue from the policy result.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Modes</h2>
    <p>
      Product docs should eventually distinguish planning, building,
      verification, and general question-answering modes so the tool surface
      matches the user intent.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
